Concrete findings:

1. Mechanism-level essentials vs conveniences  
   The local corpus treats these as load-bearing, not decorative: stage order, delayed-threshold behavior, pump/amplifier hierarchy, time-scale separation, phase/sign structure, and the tiny trigger role. The strongest evidence is Tao’s literal delayed-abrupt-transfer chain and the explicit note that the signs are “not cosmetic” and that the shell transfer times shrink summably ([exploration 001](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md#L241), [exploration 001](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md#L465), [exploration 001](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md#L487).  
   “Admissible leakage” is not part of Tao’s averaged mechanism itself; it is the mission-level obstruction threshold the new branch wants to test ([MISSION.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-MISSION.md#L71), [CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L71)).

2. Support and packet identity  
   The local record does not support “single Fourier mode” as the right support notion for this branch. It explicitly keeps the support question open among single modes, conjugate-complete pairs, and packet-level objects, but the rest of the corpus leans toward packet-level/helical packet language as the real mission object ([CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L82), [MISSION.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-MISSION.md#L75), [planner.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md#L13)).  
   Conjugate completion is treated as required bookkeeping in Fourier space, not as a substitute for packet identity ([planner-chains/chain-02](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md#L20), [judgment chain 03](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md#L33)).  
   Best local reading: use a helical packet / packet-level object, with conjugate completion as part of canonicalization.

3. Canonicalization and representation rules  
   The strongest local rule is: separate true symmetries from canonicalization choices from genuinely different modeling choices. That is explicit in the winning chain and its judgment ([CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L111), [judgment chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md#L25)).  
   The record treats these as substantive, not cosmetic: real-valuedness makes conjugate completion matter; rescaling is only harmless if full NS scaling is fixed; helical basis choice and packet regrouping can change the mathematics; phase conventions, amplitude hierarchy, and time windows must be predeclared ([attacks/chain-01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md#L17), [judgment chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md#L21), [winning chain](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/winning-chain.md#L47)).  
   So “cosmetic” changes are only the ones that stay inside a fixed canonicalization policy. Threshold retuning, packet regrouping, and phase cherry-picking are not cosmetic in this corpus.

4. Sharp Tao-likeness discriminator  
   Yes, the inherited record already supports a sharper discriminator than a generic sparse or multiscale packet idea. It is not a scalar score; it is a feature ledger plus exact interaction template plus admissibility sheet. The discriminator is essentially: a near-isolated five-role delayed-threshold circuit with ordered couplings, fixed packet semantics, fixed canonical presentation, and bounded spectator leakage under exact triadic/Leray dynamics ([exploration 001](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md#L264), [final report](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md#L55), [CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L71)).  
