/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:19:- The chain acts as if one can simply "choose" a leakage functional, but the whole mission already knows that this choice is dangerous. Ratios like off-graph interaction strength divided by on-graph interaction strength are not automatically invariant under packetization, normalization, basis choice, or time-window choice.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:21:- The proposed closure conventions are not clean alternatives on the same footing. Exact Fourier support closure, helical triad closure, and conjugate completion are different layers of bookkeeping, not one menu of mutually exclusive rules.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:26:- The kill condition is too late and too weak. If no invariant leakage functional exists, this chain should not "redirect" after trying Step 1; it should admit that it was downstream of an unresolved prerequisite from the start.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:32:- "Smallest candidate packets" is a hidden thesis. A leakage lower bound proved only for minimal packets may say nothing about larger packets with redundancy, compensating geometry, or distributed role assignment.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:33:- The ledger language encourages overcounting. A mode can be kinematically forced yet dynamically negligible, cancelled, or damped on the time scale that matters for Tao-like behavior.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- "Finite-packet non-closure" is not automatically a stronger obstruction. It only kills one model class. The mission target is near-closed Tao-like behavior, not necessarily strict finite packet closure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:47:- The plan assumes exact coefficient identities and projection geometry can produce sign-definite inequalities. In helical triad algebra, many terms are sign-indefinite and phase-sensitive. The generic outcome is cancellation structure, not monotone leakage.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:52:- The kill condition only asks whether every spectator term can cancel simultaneously. That is too binary. The more realistic failure mode is softer: no uniform positive lower bound survives, but no explicit arbitrarily-small-leakage family is yet found either.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:71:- The chain presents a false dichotomy: either positive infimum leakage or an explicit vanishing-leakage family. There is a large middle ground where leakage decays along families but not cleanly enough to be theorem-ready.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:73:- An explicit low-leakage family is not yet a serious anti-obstruction result unless it also preserves the Tao-like role logic over a meaningful time window. Instantaneous low leakage is weaker than near-circuit dynamics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:82:- Dependency inversion: this chain really depends on Chain 04. Without a stable object definition, "leakage" can be tuned by bookkeeping and the whole program becomes selection-biased.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:86:- Redundancy risk: unless it delivers a genuinely invariant lower bound or a sharp low-leakage family, it overlaps heavily with the mission's already-known "unavoidable spectator couplings" story and adds little beyond nicer packaging.
