/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/exact-rewrite-architecture-screening/cross-currency-claims-need-an-explicit-transfer-lemma-back-to-the-full-lei-bundle.md:11:Each such claim needs an explicit transfer lemma that names how the surrogate
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The weakness is that it tries to turn a hard object-definition and theorem-calibration problem into a search-and-score problem too early. In this mission, that is dangerous. If "near-closed Tao circuit" has not already survived the Chain 04 invariance audit, then Step 1 just invents a proxy and the rest of the chain optimizes that proxy. Then Step 5 overclaims in both directions: a small-packet partial mimic is treated as a clean kill of the firewall idea, while small-family failure is treated as informative obstruction. Neither inference is earned by the current design.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The score mixes fundamentally different requirements: sign pattern, channel separation, rotor dominance, spectator leakage, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not obviously commensurable. A scalar score can hide the fact that one catastrophic failure is being compensated by two cosmetic wins.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:20:- The score is vulnerable to representation dependence unless Chain 04 has already frozen the invariant object. Phase conventions, packet regrouping, normalization, and helical bookkeeping can all move a candidate's apparent "likeness" without changing the mathematics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:23:Failure mode: Step 1 produces a tidy scorecard that later stages start treating as the mission object, even though it is only one ad hoc surrogate for that object.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The chain says "full conjugate completion," which is necessary but not sufficient. The real burden is exact closure under all forced interactions, not just mirror completion. Once that is imposed honestly, the "small family" may stop being small.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:44:- This step overlaps heavily with Chain 02. Once the chain builds an exact coupling ledger, classifies spectators, and ranks by leakage-like criteria, it is already doing a weakened version of the lower-bound chain before it reaches any construction-specific dynamics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The phrase "reduced exact amplitude systems" is the crux. If the candidate is only near-closed, what exactly is being integrated? A truly exact closed packet, or a reduced subsystem obtained by dropping forced modes? If it is the latter, the dynamic test is already compromised.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:57:- Delayed-threshold behavior is stiff and phase-sensitive. One or two hand-picked trajectories are not strong evidence. A candidate could "work" only under fine-tuned initial phases or fail once viscosity, shell spacing, or amplitude normalization are varied honestly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:Chain 03 is supposed to coexist with Chain 04, but in practice it tries to bypass it. If the stable definition of "near-closed Tao circuit" is not already fixed, then "Tao-likeness" becomes whatever this chain's score function says it is. That makes the search output hard to trust and hard to compare with the other chains.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The mission asks about an exact no-near-closed-Tao-circuit statement. A tiny packet that partially mimics pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic does not by itself refute the broader obstruction. It may only show that one naive formulation was too strict.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:90:Steps 1 through 3 already revolve around leakage, forced spectators, and exact interaction ledgers. The difference only appears once Step 4 starts dynamic testing. So much of the chain duplicates the lower-bound route but with a looser metric and stronger dependence on search heuristics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:111:That is not obviously the "fastest" route inside a 3-5 exploration mission budget, especially when Chain 04 is supposed to gate the object definition first.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:118:- Even failure could be useful if the output is written modestly as a diagnostic about small exact packets, not as a global theorem surrogate.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
