/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/tao-circuit-feature-ledger/the-tiny-trigger-role-is-dynamically-central.md:13:- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/library-inbox/step-001-exploration-001-feature-ledger.md`
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain points at a real mission-aligned pressure point: exact Navier-Stokes may realize some desired Tao-role channels while still failing to isolate them. But the chain treated "leakage" as if it could be chosen by bookkeeping, delayed the geometry and helicity adversary too long, and moved too quickly from forced couplings to a dynamical obstruction claim.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:7:The right repair is not to discard the chain. It is to narrow it into a downstream quantitative test that only starts after a stable near-closure object is fixed, uses one invariant dynamical observable, treats minimal packets as calibration rather than theorem scope, and allows an honest middle outcome where the leakage route itself fails to produce a class-uniform theorem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the load-bearing criticism. The original Step 1 acted as if one could simply choose a leakage functional and closure rule, but this mission already identified object-definition instability as a first-order risk. Also, exact Fourier support closure, helical triad bookkeeping, and conjugate completion are not interchangeable options on one level. The refined chain should therefore begin only after one stable near-closure object has been frozen, ideally by Chain 04.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:39:The original finish allowed only two clean endings: positive leakage bound or explicit vanishing-leakage family. That misses the likely middle case where the route fails because the observable is not invariant enough, the cancellations destroy coercivity, or the bound depends too strongly on packet-class choices. The refined chain should permit that meta-obstruction as a presentable output.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:41:### 6. The whole chain risks redundancy unless it earns an invariant lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family, or a precise obstruction to the leakage route itself
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:45:This warning is fair, but it is not a refutation. The chain does overlap with the already-known "forced spectators exist" story if it stops at a prettier ledger. Still, a sharp failure diagnosis can be valuable here. If the refined chain can say exactly why no class-uniform leakage theorem emerges, that is more than redundant packaging.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:52:2. It chooses one invariant dynamical leakage observable before any ledger is built.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:54:4. It allows three honest endings: a restricted-class positive lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family that preserves Tao-role logic over a stated window, or a precise obstruction showing why leakage-based arguments do not yield a presentable theorem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:64:- The most plausible success mode is not a universal no-near-closure theorem, but either a restricted-class leakage bound or a clean diagnosis of why the leakage program cannot support such a theorem without stronger hypotheses.
