+# Meta Note - Step 2 Exploration 001
+
+## What Worked
+
+- The local record already contained a bounded candidate split once the
+  Step-1 packet freeze and the exact-NS intervention map were read together.
+- Keeping `projection rigidity` as a mechanism note instead of promoting it as
+  a fourth candidate avoided confusing enforcement with object definition.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- When a branch wants exact candidate notions rather than slogans, force each
+  candidate to name one packet class, one finite window, one threshold
+  language, and one canonical sign / amplitude / phase sheet before arguing
+  about usefulness.
+
+## Caution
+
+- A pro-near-circuit-friendly behavioral candidate is honest only if it is
+  written in exact projected channel data. As soon as it imports Tao's averaged
+  coefficients directly, it stops being a real exact-NS object.
